            <description>Occasionally, I need to spin up a few local virtual machines on my Windows 10 laptop to test a networking concept. Building a practical multi-machine configuration can be challenging. For me, this typically means:
   The VM host can connect to the guest VMs.
  The guest VMs can connect to the host.
  The guest VMs can connect to each other.</description>

